# AKR Group Monorepo Rules

You are an expert full-stack developer working on a high-performance monorepo.

## Project Structure
- `apps/web`: Next.js frontend (SSR, Tailwind, TypeScript)
- `apps/api`: NestJS backend (PostgreSQL, Redis, TypeScript)
- `packages/*`: Shared internal packages (UI, Config, Utils)

## General Guidelines
- Use TypeScript for all code.
- Follow Clean Architecture and SOLID principles.
- Use atomic commits and descriptive messages.
- Ensure all components are responsive and wowed by design.

## Frontend Specifics (apps/web)
- Use Next.js App Router and Server Components.
- Styling: Tailwind CSS.
- Component Design: Premium aesthetics, glassmorphism, smooth animations.

## Backend Specifics (apps/api)
- Use NestJS modules, controllers, and services.
- Database: TypeORM/Prisma with PostgreSQL.
- Caching: Redis for performance.
- Validation: Class-validator and class-transformer.
